pull_request.title: Add XMSS-SHA256_{10, 16, 20}_192 parameters
pull_request.body:
Signed-off-by: Duc Tri Nguyen <dnguye69@gmu.edu>

<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->

- Add additional XMSS parameters to meet NIST SP 800 208. 
- Add emoji to Table parameters `sig_stfl_xmss.h`, I hope it's helpful and save developer time. 
- Add KATs. 
- Add tests.

pull_request.title: macOS build: search for arm64 openssl library in homebrew before x86_64
pull_request.body:
<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->

Searches for the arm64 openssl v1.1 library BEFORE the x86_64 one

Installed arm systems may still have x64 implementations present, but the reverse is unlikely. In most cases this change will have no effect, but on my macOS environment I noticed the old x86_64 libraries were being picked up by liboqs build

The fix simply reverses the order of the check
